5:
He wanted this to go to his child. The
eldest daughter.
7:
I see... Thank you very much. This is
the last item we had of his, and... 
It wasn't in the will, you see.
18:
How about a break? I've whipped up
some tea—let's drink it while it's hot!
28:
Corinna. Please don't look at me. 
It's embarrassing.
32:
Hehe, sorry. It's hard not to stare!
That outfit just looks so perfect on
you.
42:
P-please. Enough about the clothes.
I need to focus on work.
46:
So these voices you hear, Falsche...
They're not the ghosts exactly, are
they?
50:
No. The best way to describe them.
Would be as lingering echoes.
53:
If I listen closely, I can hear them.
Here and there. Whispering. Faintly.
55:
All I do is lend an ear to them. To
their last words. And then I pass
them on. To those they left behind.
65:
No. I can't talk to them. They talk to
me. And I listen.
69:
I'm sorry. I can't explain it any better.
I don't know how it works.
73:
I think I more or less got it! No
worries. Right, Stella?
76: Yes. I understand. More or less.
84: Hey, you. Are you the salvager?
90:
...Huh. Sorry, it's just you don't look
how I thought you would.
93:
I-I'm currently rebranding myself.
Trying out something new.
95: I see. Sorry if I was rude there.
97:
Anyway. Was wondering if you could
look at this. It's my old pal's sword.
101:
Oh, perhaps it would be best if the
two of us stepped away for a
moment.
103:
No, I don't mind. I'm the one who
barged in suddenly.
106:
Okay. Let me hear. What this sword
has to say.
110:
...Can't even hold a sword anymore.
Can't speak, can't stand.
111:
Before the end...
Before I go, I just...
112:
I want to go on another crazy,
ridiculous adventure with him.
Sword in hand, off to who knows
where...
115:
The owner of this sword. Until the
very moment he died. He wanted to
go on an adventure with you.
118:
You should have this sword. And you
should take it with you. When you
travel.
120:
Go somewhere far. Do something
crazy and ridiculous. That was his
final wish.
123:
Is that so... Well, I'm grateful to have
it, if that's what he wanted.
124:
Never hurts to have a spare sword, I
suppose... Could come in handy on
an adventure.
145:
Stella's right. You are amazing!
Watching you work is a treat.
153:
You helped that man so much, just
by talking to him! It was like you
exorcized a spirit that was haunting
him!
155:
All because you told him what he
needed to hear.
164:
Hehe! My, my. What a triumphant
look on your face! Glad to see you
admit it.
